{
  "texts": [
    "The main hurdle for utilizing protein sequence-based language models, such as ProtBERT [35], was heavy computing resource requirements.",
    "To comprehend the complex and long sequence of a protein, it needed heavy and large architectures and an intensive pre-training process.",
    "The DLM-DTI mitigated the computational burden caused by the protein encoder, by using a knowledgeadaptation.",
    "DLM-DTI achieved improved AUPRC performance, especially in Binding DB (0.63 ∼ 3.38%), and BIOSNAP (1.44 ∼ 1.9%) datasets.",
    "The most interesting point was that DLM-DTI utilized only 25% of parameters (86.7 million) compared to the previous state-of-the-art model, Kang et al."
  ]
}